---
---
<section class="page-container section-spacer" data-orb="4">
  <div class="geo-divider">
    <span class="geo-circle" style="background: var(--color-geo-teal);"></span>
    <span class="geo-circle" style="background: var(--color-geo-amber);"></span>
    <span class="geo-circle" style="background: var(--color-geo-blue);"></span>
  </div>
  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr; gap: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow fade-in">features</p>
      <h2 class="fade-in-up delay-1">Everything you need.</h2>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="fade-in-up delay-2" style="padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.375rem; font-size: 1rem;">Notes & diary</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7;">Rich text, markdown, mood and energy tracking, full-text search, encrypted at rest.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in-up delay-3" style="padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.375rem; font-size: 1rem;">Calendar & time-blocking</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7;">Visual month grid and day timeline. Real multi-day events (a whole vacation as one entry, shown correctly on every day it spans). Habit-linked events, color-coded categories.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in-up delay-4" style="padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.375rem; font-size: 1rem;">Tasks with AI breakdown</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7;">Vague intentions become tiny concrete steps with time estimates -- the first one always small enough to start in under 5 minutes. Nested subtasks, priorities, due dates.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in-up delay-5" style="padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.375rem; font-size: 1rem;">Habits with forgiving streaks</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7;">Simple tap-to-log habits, or scheduled routine/fitness time blocks. Tiny versions count. Archive and restore anytime.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in-up delay-6" style="padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.375rem; font-size: 1rem;">Budget</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7;">Income and expenses in your own currency. Recurring bills auto-populate your calendar like a habit does. Tap-to-repeat chips for the coffee run.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in-up delay-7" style="padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.375rem; font-size: 1rem;">Reminders & alarms</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7;">One-shot reminders or a distinct alarm sound on any task, event, or habit. Delivered via Telegram and/or a native desktop notification.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in-up delay-8" style="padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.375rem; font-size: 1rem;">AI assistant with tools</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7;">Creates events, logs habits, breaks down tasks, logs expenses, remembers facts -- real tool-calling parity with the hand-built UI, not a separate weaker path. OpenAI or local Ollama.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in-up delay-8" style="padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.375rem; font-size: 1rem;">Telegram remote access</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7;">Pair once with a code. Log habits, dump tasks from your phone. Messages queue while you sleep.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in-up delay-8" style="padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.375rem; font-size: 1rem;">Insights and correlations</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7;">Mood trends, habit heatmaps, Pearson correlations. Ask for an LLM-narrated weekly reflection any time, in neutral language.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in-up delay-8" style="padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.375rem; font-size: 1rem;">Security first</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7;">OS keyring auth, field-level Fernet encryption, CSP headers, rate limiting, loopback-only binding.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in-up delay-8" style="padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.375rem; font-size: 1rem;">Runs anywhere, updates safely</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7;">One-command Docker, or a native installer for Mac, Windows, or Linux -- no admin rights needed. Updates apply one version at a time, database backed up automatically first.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
